{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":824,"text":"I've been a critical care EMT for the past\nseven years in Suffolk County, New York."},{"time":4517,"text":"I've been a first responder in a number of incidents"},{"time":6359,"text":"ranging from car accidents to Hurricane Sandy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9677,"text":"If you are like most people, death might be"},{"time":11421,"text":"one of your greatest fears."},{"time":13389,"text":"Some of us will see it coming."},{"time":14810,"text":"Some of us won't."},{"time":16809,"text":"There is a little-known documented medical term"},{"time":18913,"text":"called impending doom."},{"time":20859,"text":"It's almost a symptom."},{"time":22186,"text":"As a medical provider, I'm trained to respond"},{"time":23919,"text":"to this symptom like any other,"},{"time":25741,"text":"so when a patient having a heart attack looks at me"},{"time":27282,"text":"and says, \"I'm going to die today,\""},{"time":29510,"text":"we are trained to reevaluate the patient's condition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33236,"text":"Throughout my career, I have responded"},{"time":35382,"text":"to a number of incidents where the patient"},{"time":37328,"text":"had minutes left to live"},{"time":38965,"text":"and there was nothing I could do for them."},{"time":42090,"text":"With this, I was faced with a dilemma:"},{"time":44876,"text":"Do I tell the dying that they are about to face death,"},{"time":48588,"text":"or do I lie to them to comfort them?"},{"time":51615,"text":"Early in my career, I faced this dilemma"},{"time":53808,"text":"by simply lying."},{"time":55366,"text":"I was afraid."},{"time":57295,"text":"I was afraid if I told them the truth,"},{"time":59635,"text":"that they would die in terror, in fear,"},{"time":62976,"text":"just grasping for those last moments of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66182,"text":"That all changed with one incident."},{"time":68950,"text":"Five years ago, I responded to a motorcycle accident."},{"time":71799,"text":"The rider had suffered critical, critical injuries."},{"time":74601,"text":"As I assessed him, I realized that there was nothing"},{"time":77432,"text":"that could be done for him,"},{"time":79399,"text":"and like so many other cases,\nhe looked me in the eye"},{"time":82664,"text":"and asked that question: \"Am I going to die?\""},{"time":87076,"text":"In that moment, I decided to do something different."},{"time":90582,"text":"I decided to tell him the truth."},{"time":93462,"text":"I decided to tell him that he was going to die"},{"time":96556,"text":"and that there was nothing I could do for him."},{"time":99820,"text":"His reaction shocked me to this day."},{"time":103596,"text":"He simply laid back and had a look"},{"time":105501,"text":"of acceptance on his face."},{"time":107927,"text":"He was not met with that terror or fear"},{"time":109630,"text":"that I thought he would be."},{"time":112010,"text":"He simply laid there, and as I looked into his eyes,"},{"time":115222,"text":"I saw inner peace and acceptance."},{"time":117950,"text":"From that moment forward, I decided"},{"time":119688,"text":"it was not my place to comfort the dying with my lies."},{"time":124402,"text":"Having responded to many cases since then"},{"time":127147,"text":"where patients were in their last moments"},{"time":129655,"text":"and there was nothing I could do for them,"},{"time":131511,"text":"in almost every case,"},{"time":133150,"text":"they have all had the same reaction to the truth,"},{"time":136484,"text":"of inner peace and acceptance."},{"time":138550,"text":"In fact, there are three patterns"},{"time":140972,"text":"I have observed in all these cases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145247,"text":"The first pattern always kind of shocked me."},{"time":148903,"text":"Regardless of religious belief or cultural background,"},{"time":152840,"text":"there's a need for forgiveness."},{"time":155675,"text":"Whether they call it sin"},{"time":157221,"text":"or they simply say they have a regret,"},{"time":160090,"text":"their guilt is universal."},{"time":162503,"text":"I had once cared for an elderly gentleman"},{"time":163899,"text":"who was having a massive heart attack."},{"time":166317,"text":"As I prepared myself and my equipment"},{"time":168443,"text":"for his imminent cardiac arrest,"},{"time":171368,"text":"I began to tell the patient of his imminent demise."},{"time":175721,"text":"He already knew by my tone\nof voice and body language."},{"time":178719,"text":"As I placed the defibrillator pads on his chest,"},{"time":181385,"text":"prepping for what was going to happen,"},{"time":183289,"text":"he looked me in the eye and said,"},{"time":185817,"text":"\"I wish I had spent more time with\nmy children and grandchildren"},{"time":188517,"text":"instead of being selfish with my time.\""},{"time":191588,"text":"Faced with imminent death,"},{"time":193920,"text":"all he wanted was forgiveness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196854,"text":"The second pattern I observe"},{"time":198742,"text":"is the need for remembrance."},{"time":201030,"text":"Whether it was to be remembered in my thoughts"},{"time":203287,"text":"or their loved ones', they needed to feel"},{"time":205001,"text":"that they would be living on."},{"time":207150,"text":"There's a need for immortality"},{"time":209474,"text":"within the hearts and thoughts of their loved ones,"},{"time":212118,"text":"myself, my crew, or anyone around."},{"time":215391,"text":"Countless times, I have had a \npatient look me in the eyes"},{"time":218282,"text":"and say, \"Will you remember me?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":222220,"text":"The final pattern I observe"},{"time":224672,"text":"always touched me the deepest, to the soul."},{"time":227900,"text":"The dying need to know that their life had meaning."},{"time":231440,"text":"They need to know that they did not waste their life"},{"time":234222,"text":"on meaningless tasks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237170,"text":"This came to me very, very early in my career."},{"time":240319,"text":"I had responded to a call."},{"time":242408,"text":"There was a female in her late 50s"},{"time":244332,"text":"severely pinned within a vehicle."},{"time":246390,"text":"She had been t-boned at a high rate of speed,"},{"time":250068,"text":"critical, critical condition."},{"time":252500,"text":"As the fire department worked\nto remove her from the car,"},{"time":254740,"text":"I climbed in to begin to render care."},{"time":257707,"text":"As we talked, she had said to me,"},{"time":260767,"text":"\"There was so much more\nI wanted to do with my life.\""},{"time":263980,"text":"She had felt she had not left her mark on this Earth."},{"time":267832,"text":"As we talked further, it would turn out"},{"time":269789,"text":"that she was a mother of two adopted children"},{"time":272197,"text":"who were both on their way to medical school."},{"time":275312,"text":"Because of her, two children"},{"time":277382,"text":"had a chance they never would have had otherwise"},{"time":280100,"text":"and would go on to save lives in the medical field"},{"time":282321,"text":"as medical doctors."},{"time":284683,"text":"It would end up taking 45 minutes"},{"time":286472,"text":"to free her from the vehicle."},{"time":288339,"text":"However, she perished prior to freeing her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292569,"text":"I believed what you saw in the movies:"},{"time":294661,"text":"when you're in those last moments"},{"time":295945,"text":"that it's strictly terror, fear."},{"time":298857,"text":"I have come to realize,\nregardless of the circumstance,"},{"time":301535,"text":"it's generally met with peace and acceptance,"},{"time":304448,"text":"that it's the littlest things, the littlest moments,"},{"time":308140,"text":"the littlest things you brought into the world"},{"time":311704,"text":"that give you peace in those final moments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314633,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316665,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}